WELCOME TO PICO MUNDO

4
00:00:26,190 --> 00:00:27,244
My name is Odd Thomas.

5
00:00:27,279 --> 00:00:31,029
Though in this age when fame is the
altar at which most people worship.

6
00:00:31,064 --> 00:00:32,537
I'm not sure why you should care.

7
00:00:32,572 --> 00:00:34,988
I'm not a celebrity.
I'm not the child of a celebrity.

8
00:00:35,023 --> 00:00:36,777
I've never been married to,
abused by,

9
00:00:36,812 --> 00:00:38,530
or provided a kidney to a celebrity.

10
00:00:38,565 --> 00:00:39,858
Green Moon Bowling

11
00:00:42,572 --> 00:00:46,020
But I do lead an unusual life.

12
00:00:53,531 --> 00:00:55,605
Penny Kalisto.

13
00:01:05,615 --> 00:01:08,080
My name really is Odd.

14
00:01:08,115 --> 00:01:11,488
According to my mother, it was
a screw-up on my birth certificate.

15
00:01:11,523 --> 00:01:14,861
She says I was supposed to be called
Todd, after a Lithuanian uncle.

16
00:01:15,282 --> 00:01:17,539
My father insists my name
was always Odd...

17
00:01:17,574 --> 00:01:20,821
and he notes that all of
my uncles are Bulgarian.

18
00:01:21,324 --> 00:01:24,091
My father claims
my mother is insane.

19
00:01:24,126 --> 00:01:26,860
My mother, of course,
begs to differ.

20
00:01:27,575 --> 00:01:32,777
My abilities are a gift from God!

21
00:01:33,533 --> 00:01:35,489
My father won that argument.

22
00:01:36,742 --> 00:01:40,403
I was 12 years old when they finally
locked her up and threw away the key.

23
00:01:45,409 --> 00:01:49,569
I've come to believe that
my mother and I share certain...

24
00:01:49,659 --> 00:01:51,082
abilities.

25
00:01:51,117 --> 00:01:53,826
Since I don't want to be locked up
with the key thrown away...

26
00:01:53,861 --> 00:01:57,985
I've pretty much kept mine a secret.

27
00:02:05,909 --> 00:02:07,368
Odd Thomas.

28
00:02:07,403 --> 00:02:08,792
Hello, Harlo.

29
00:02:08,827 --> 00:02:10,375
Long time, no see.

30
00:02:10,410 --> 00:02:13,327
Whoa! Whoa! Hey, hey.
Come on, man. No touchy, no feely.

31
00:02:13,362 --> 00:02:16,401
- Sorry, but I love this car.
- I know.

32
00:02:16,436 --> 00:02:19,440
It's too bad a car
can't love you back.

33
00:02:22,077 --> 00:02:24,304
What's wrong, Odd?
There anything I can do?

34
00:02:24,339 --> 00:02:26,531
No, it's something
you've already done.

35
00:02:27,369 --> 00:02:29,509
Hey! Hey! Come on- oh, Odd.
No fooling around, man.

36
00:02:29,544 --> 00:02:31,650
- Give me my keys.
- Her blood is in your pocket.

37
00:02:33,620 --> 00:02:35,866
Most people would think
that's a weird thing to say...

38
00:02:35,901 --> 00:02:38,113
but you don't think
it's very weird, do you, Harlo?

39
00:02:44,995 --> 00:02:46,239
On that night...

40
00:02:47,704 --> 00:02:50,204
you took a piece of white felt...

41
00:02:50,239 --> 00:02:52,127
and after killing Penny...

42
00:02:52,162 --> 00:02:54,870
you collected some of her blood.

43
00:02:54,905 --> 00:02:56,919
And now it's dry...

44
00:02:56,954 --> 00:03:00,700
and stiff and
brittle like a cracker...

45
00:03:01,538 --> 00:03:05,283
and it's still in your pocket.

46
00:03:12,996 --> 00:03:15,705
In moments like these,
pity tears at me.

47
00:03:15,740 --> 00:03:18,379
And a kind of madness
comes over me...

48
00:03:18,414 --> 00:03:21,122
forcing me to hunt people
like Harlo Landerson...

49
00:03:21,157 --> 00:03:25,068
who I have no pity for whatsoever.

50
00:03:42,373 --> 00:03:44,448
Sorry, Mrs. Curtees!

51
00:03:46,332 --> 00:03:47,908
Sorry, Saleen!

52
00:04:21,250 --> 00:04:23,000
What the hell are you doing?

53
00:04:23,035 --> 00:04:25,205
Mom, what's going on?

54
00:04:29,459 --> 00:04:31,331
Stevie, run honey, run!

55
00:04:39,876 --> 00:04:40,906
Come here!

56
00:04:49,793 --> 00:04:52,496
My life is filled with guys
like Harlo Landerson.

57
00:04:55,835 --> 00:04:58,122
And since I like my face
just the way it is...

58
00:04:59,378 --> 00:05:01,036
I learned how to handle myself.

59
00:05:17,795 --> 00:05:22,287
I may see dead people, but then,
by God, I do something about it.

60
00:05:23,129 --> 00:05:24,969
Hey. Hey!

61
00:05:25,004 --> 00:05:26,927
Shift down, man! Go easy.

62
00:05:26,962 --> 00:05:29,877
I'm sorry, sir,
but I don't have a "go easy" gear.

63
00:05:31,046 --> 00:05:32,796
You should probably get that looked at.

64
00:05:32,831 --> 00:05:34,345
Now, Officer Eckles...

65
00:05:34,380 --> 00:05:35,470
does being a police officer

66
00:05:35,505 --> 00:05:37,171
give you the right to beat
the shit out of people?

67
00:05:37,206 --> 00:05:38,803
Not at all, Officer Varner.

68
00:05:38,838 --> 00:05:40,828
But it is one of
the perks of the job.

69
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:51,039
I believe in a higher power
and the afterlife.

70
00:05:52,713 --> 00:05:54,586
Call me strange.

71
00:05:55,631 --> 00:05:56,845
Others do.

72
00:05:56,880 --> 00:05:58,752
He's so strange.

73
00:06:01,131 --> 00:06:02,471
Don't worry, Penny.

74
00:06:02,506 --> 00:06:05,922
I think where you're going
is a home for the spirit...

75
00:06:05,957 --> 00:06:09,585
and it's filled with
kindness and wonder.

76
00:06:10,714 --> 00:06:12,587
I'm sorry, Penny.

77
00:06:13,131 --> 00:06:15,702
I'm sorry your life was so short.

78
00:06:26,257 --> 00:06:27,915
The dead don't talk.

79
00:06:28,757 --> 00:06:30,831
I don't know why.

80
00:06:35,425 --> 00:06:36,722
Here we are again.

81
00:06:36,757 --> 00:06:40,005
Busted furniture and
shattered glass everywhere.

82
00:06:41,966 --> 00:06:44,015
Most of it was not my fault.

83
00:06:44,050 --> 00:06:47,446
Except the panda bear lamp
and the Biffy the Clown mirror.

84
00:06:47,481 --> 00:06:50,806
- That was this guy.
- Why didn't you come to me first..

85
00:06:50,841 --> 00:06:54,675
give me a chance to find a way
to get Harlo to entrap himself?

86
00:06:54,710 --> 00:06:55,807
Whenever we do it that way,

87
00:06:55,842 --> 00:06:57,967
it's always more efficient
and less destructive.

88
00:06:58,002 --> 00:07:00,092
Yes, I know but he had
to be stopped right now...

89
00:07:00,127 --> 00:07:02,297
or he was gonna do it again soon.

90
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:05,510
That's what Penny wanted to tell me.
That's why she hadn't left yet.

91
00:07:05,545 --> 00:07:08,957
Son, you so complicate my life.

92
00:07:11,759 --> 00:07:13,003
Look.

93
00:07:14,801 --> 00:07:15,891
Besides her blood...

94
00:07:15,926 --> 00:07:19,885
Harlo had these photos of Penny
post-mortem in his wallet.

95
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:22,673
If there's any fuss about
how you pegged Harlo...

96
00:07:22,708 --> 00:07:25,427
just say he opened up
his wallet to pay off a bet.

97
00:07:25,462 --> 00:07:28,219
Five bucks on
yesterday's Dodger's game...

98
00:07:28,254 --> 00:07:30,377
the photos fell out,
you saw em-

99
00:07:30,412 --> 00:07:32,500
He ran and naturally,
I gave chase.

100
00:07:33,136 --> 00:07:34,380
Naturally.

101
00:08:24,389 --> 00:08:28,076
Save me!

102
00:08:28,111 --> 00:08:31,729
Save us!

103
00:08:31,764 --> 00:08:33,701
- Save
- Us!

104
00:08:33,736 --> 00:08:35,623
- Save..
- Us!

105
00:08:35,658 --> 00:08:37,511
Save you from who?

106
00:08:40,098 --> 00:08:41,342
Who is that?

107
00:08:42,390 --> 00:08:43,763
Who is it?

108
00:09:21,558 --> 00:09:23,134
Evil is coming.

109
00:09:23,641 --> 00:09:26,889
And it's up to me to figure out
who's gonna be holding the gun.

110
00:09:27,933 --> 00:09:29,391
Morning, Elvis.

111
00:09:30,226 --> 00:09:31,107
Pico Mundo Grill
CLOSED

112
00:09:31,142 --> 00:09:32,774
So much of my life
is out of my controI.

113
00:09:32,809 --> 00:09:36,351
I would have gone 7 kinds of
crazy if I hadn't simplified.

114
00:09:36,386 --> 00:09:40,018
So I have no motorized vehicles,
no homeownership...

115
00:09:40,053 --> 00:09:43,018
no insurance,
and no grand ambitions.

116
00:09:43,053 --> 00:09:44,179
Ladies.

117
00:09:44,601 --> 00:09:46,108
Eggs! Wreck em and stretch em!

118
00:09:46,143 --> 00:09:48,768
"Wreck em" means scrambled,
and "stretch em" means...

119
00:09:48,803 --> 00:09:49,983
add an extra egg.

120
00:09:50,018 --> 00:09:51,441
Cardiac shingles and hash browns!

121
00:09:51,476 --> 00:09:54,601
"Cardiac shingles"
are toast with lots of butter.

122
00:09:54,636 --> 00:09:56,328
And hash browns...

123
00:09:56,363 --> 00:09:57,984
are just hash browns.

124
00:09:58,019 --> 00:10:00,720
Not every word
we use is diner lingo.

125
00:10:02,102 --> 00:10:03,608
Just as not every short-order cook

126
00:10:03,643 --> 00:10:07,811
is an undercover detective
for dead people.

127
00:10:07,846 --> 00:10:09,268
Duck.

128
00:10:15,311 --> 00:10:18,609
That is Stormy Lewellyn.

129
00:10:18,644 --> 00:10:23,137
Stormy and I are destined
to be together forever.

130
00:10:25,103 --> 00:10:26,477
GYPSY MUMMY ALL SEEING EYE

131
00:10:27,394 --> 00:10:31,554
You are destined
to be together forever.

132
00:10:34,478 --> 00:10:37,098
Hey, Chief.
Tummy Tickler coming at ya.

133
00:10:41,146 --> 00:10:43,562
You know, I'm still not happy
about what you did yesterday, Oddie.

134
00:10:43,597 --> 00:10:44,813
You could have
gotten yourself killed.

135
00:10:44,848 --> 00:10:47,486
I am not afraid of death.

136
00:10:47,521 --> 00:10:50,010
Of course, I'm not ready to go
on a date with him, either.

137
00:10:56,479 --> 00:10:58,147
Would you throw yourself
off a cliff for me?

138
00:10:58,182 --> 00:10:59,029
Of course I would.

139
00:10:59,064 --> 00:11:01,897
Into a river of razor blades
and lemon juice?

140
00:11:01,932 --> 00:11:03,112
Absolutely.

141
00:11:03,147 --> 00:11:05,522
Of course, I'd like to know
the reasoning behind such a request..

142
00:11:05,557 --> 00:11:07,570
but, fortunately for me...

143
00:11:07,605 --> 00:11:10,939
you reek of intelligence
and integrity.

144
00:11:10,974 --> 00:11:13,231
And you reek of peach shampoo.

145
00:11:13,266 --> 00:11:15,636
Just the way I like you.

146
00:11:16,898 --> 00:11:19,030
- Chief.
- Morning, Stormy.

147
00:11:19,065 --> 00:11:21,356
What's with
the cat-ate-the-canary smile?

148
00:11:21,391 --> 00:11:23,229
Tonight is date night.

149
00:11:23,981 --> 00:11:26,268
So you think you're
gonna get yourself some, huh?

150
00:11:26,565 --> 00:11:29,606
- I wouldn't put it quite that way.
- Stormy SpeciaI.

151
00:11:29,641 --> 00:11:31,681
- Girlfriend.
- Morning, dude.

152
00:11:49,607 --> 00:11:51,240
I call them bodachs.

153
00:11:51,275 --> 00:11:52,906
Well, not to their faces, I hope.

154
00:11:52,941 --> 00:11:55,311
I never met anybody
that could see em before.

155
00:11:55,524 --> 00:11:58,234
- Neither have I.
- Everyone told me it's in my head.

156
00:11:58,269 --> 00:11:59,817
Well, you should stop
telling everyone.

157
00:11:59,852 --> 00:12:01,448
I tried telling my parents.

158
00:12:01,483 --> 00:12:03,025
If I told my parents,
I'd ve spent my whole life...

159
00:12:03,060 --> 00:12:04,916
picking winning lottery numbers.

160
00:12:04,951 --> 00:12:06,772
You can pick winning lotto numbers?

161
00:12:07,192 --> 00:12:10,026
- No, I can't. Stay on point.
- Right. Yeah.

162
00:12:10,061 --> 00:12:13,151
Yesterday, when I finally saw one...

163
00:12:13,186 --> 00:12:15,317
I gave him the finger, Homes.

164
00:12:15,352 --> 00:12:16,741
Don't you know?

165
00:12:16,776 --> 00:12:20,307
If they find out you can see them,
they will kill you.

166
00:12:26,985 --> 00:12:28,561
They will kill you.

167
00:13:04,695 --> 00:13:06,326
- Little advice?
- Yeah?

168
00:13:06,361 --> 00:13:08,327
Karla prefers chocolate to flowers

169
00:13:08,362 --> 00:13:10,862
and you should get
yourself some candles.

170
00:13:10,897 --> 00:13:11,892
Candles?

171
00:13:12,403 --> 00:13:13,980
Thanks. Good idea.

172
00:13:19,612 --> 00:13:21,244
Whew, close.

173
00:13:21,279 --> 00:13:22,946
That would have been
a little awkward.

174
00:13:22,981 --> 00:13:25,400
You two are really something.

175
00:13:25,435 --> 00:13:27,786
I don't know what, but something.

176
00:13:27,821 --> 00:13:30,321
We're weird and screwed up
but we're okay.

177
00:13:30,356 --> 00:13:31,565
I don't know.

178
00:13:31,780 --> 00:13:33,237
You are...

179
00:13:34,405 --> 00:13:35,703
so cool.

180
00:13:35,738 --> 00:13:39,405
So, you deny me my weirdness,
but agree that I'm screwed up?

181
00:13:39,440 --> 00:13:41,037
You're right.
I see your problem.

182
00:13:41,072 --> 00:13:43,363
Weirdness, it can be fun.
It can be kind of cooI.

183
00:13:43,398 --> 00:13:47,114
Screwed-up-ness, not so much.

184
00:13:47,149 --> 00:13:49,899
You are quite weird.

185
00:13:51,489 --> 00:13:54,698
- Apology accepted.
- I gotta go. Be good, you two.

186
00:13:54,733 --> 00:13:57,322
It's not me you have to worry about.

187
00:13:57,357 --> 00:13:58,650
Don't I know it.

188
00:13:59,281 --> 00:14:01,490
I gotta go to work, too, Oddie.

189
00:14:01,525 --> 00:14:03,776
- Okay.
- Later, my love.

190
00:14:14,490 --> 00:14:15,652
Stormy!

191
00:14:24,407 --> 00:14:26,149
Miss you already.

192
00:14:31,075 --> 00:14:32,825
- Living up to his name.
- Every damn day.

193
00:14:32,860 --> 00:14:34,069
Later.

194
00:14:34,491 --> 00:14:38,241
Months often pass
when I don't see a single bodach.

195
00:14:38,276 --> 00:14:39,165
When they do show up...

196
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:42,325
it's a sure sign that carnage
and bloodshed are not far behind.

197
00:14:42,360 --> 00:14:43,207
Morning.

198
00:14:43,242 --> 00:14:45,446
They don't cause it.
They feed on it.

199
00:14:46,076 --> 00:14:49,690
The more bodachs that show up,
the bigger the eventuaI feast.

200
00:14:52,117 --> 00:14:54,617
They're attracted to evil
like bees to flowers.

201
00:14:54,652 --> 00:14:57,117
They know when death is coming
and want to watch.

202
00:14:57,152 --> 00:14:59,458
They don't show up
for any ordinary death.

203
00:14:59,493 --> 00:15:03,783
They want extreme,
operatic violence and terror.

204
00:15:05,952 --> 00:15:08,869
Penny Kalisto's death
wasn't horrific enough...

205
00:15:08,904 --> 00:15:12,613
to bring a single bodach
into our world.

206
00:15:16,078 --> 00:15:19,277
This town is in serious trouble.

207
00:15:20,452 --> 00:15:22,536
- Bye, Oddie.
- See you, ladies.

208
00:15:22,571 --> 00:15:24,408
Nicolina! Levanna!

209
00:15:28,244 --> 00:15:30,947
Odd, am I really sucking
at this whole "mother" thing?

210
00:15:32,411 --> 00:15:34,460
Well, considering their
last one was a junkie...

211
00:15:34,495 --> 00:15:37,119
who left them in your lap
when you were barely 18...

212
00:15:37,154 --> 00:15:40,745
I think you rather rock, Vi.

213
00:15:40,780 --> 00:15:41,775
See you later.

214
00:15:42,328 --> 00:15:44,252
I'm heading this way, too.

215
00:15:44,287 --> 00:15:46,641
Gonna go see Madame Pearl,
get myself read.

216
00:15:46,676 --> 00:15:48,961
Personally,
I don't believe people who say...

217
00:15:48,996 --> 00:15:52,120
they can read minds or palms
and, trust me, tea leaves...

218
00:15:52,155 --> 00:15:53,836
just cloggage
in the garbage disposal.

219
00:15:53,871 --> 00:15:56,913
It's just I had this dream
last night you would not believe.

220
00:15:56,948 --> 00:16:00,663
Well, anything short of
a 9-alarm massacre, I can top.

221
00:16:00,698 --> 00:16:03,365
I'd never seen myself face-on
in a dream before.

222
00:16:04,705 --> 00:16:06,128
You saw your own face?

223
00:16:06,163 --> 00:16:09,705
Me and this guy, we were
both lying dead all busted up...

224
00:16:09,740 --> 00:16:12,407
like we'd been shot
to pieces or something.

225
00:16:17,622 --> 00:16:19,796
You know, I wouldn't worry
about it, Vi.

226
00:16:19,831 --> 00:16:21,905
I mean, have any of
your dreams ever come true?

227
00:16:22,831 --> 00:16:23,993
No.

228
00:16:24,622 --> 00:16:27,331
I know most people think
you're just quirky or weird, Odd...

229
00:16:27,366 --> 00:16:29,414
except Stormy who thinks
angels fly out of your butt.

230
00:16:29,449 --> 00:16:31,164
But I know there's more to it.

231
00:16:31,199 --> 00:16:32,713
You have a secret.

232
00:16:32,748 --> 00:16:34,671
You're either a clairvoyant...

233
00:16:34,706 --> 00:16:36,964
a psychic, a seer,
a soothsayer, or something.

234
00:16:36,999 --> 00:16:39,206
Or you got yourself some juice
with a higher power.

235
00:16:39,241 --> 00:16:40,088
And I need to know.

236
00:16:40,123 --> 00:16:41,996
Tell me the truth now, Odd.

237
00:16:42,832 --> 00:16:44,906
Do you see death in me?

238
00:16:48,165 --> 00:16:52,624
No. No, all I see
is my own insensitivity...

239
00:16:52,659 --> 00:16:56,072
and a long,
happy life for you, okay?

240
00:16:59,916 --> 00:17:03,661
Hey, Vi, the the dead guy
in your dream, what was he wearing?

241
00:17:04,416 --> 00:17:06,374
Wearing? I don't know.

242
00:17:06,409 --> 00:17:08,632
Oh! Wait. Yeah...

243
00:17:08,667 --> 00:17:13,158
a red and black shirt with
black bowling balls on it.

244
00:17:19,917 --> 00:17:22,959
One of my stranger abilities is
that when I need to find someone...

245
00:17:22,993 --> 00:17:25,507
like right now, the creepy
guy in the diner,

246
00:17:25,542 --> 00:17:29,501
I can randomly wander around, and
pretty quickly, I'll run into him.

247
00:17:29,536 --> 00:17:31,907
This is a talent for
which I have no name.

248
00:17:32,209 --> 00:17:35,126
Stormy calls it psychic magnetism.

249
00:17:35,161 --> 00:17:37,717
TIRE WORLD
Super Summer Sale

250
