is stupid and careless...

986
01:09:57,971 --> 01:09:59,586
and he's gonna get us nailed
if we don't do something.

987
01:09:59,621 --> 01:10:00,467
Relax.

988
01:10:00,502 --> 01:10:03,835
Did Robertson ever find those
photos at the mall he misplaced?

989
01:10:03,870 --> 01:10:08,328
I said, relax.
I'll take care of him.

990
01:10:19,794 --> 01:10:22,284
Stalking someone at the mall, Bern?

991
01:10:22,920 --> 01:10:24,579
Robertson, that idiot.

992
01:10:27,087 --> 01:10:28,962
We got to make it
look like an accident.

993
01:10:28,997 --> 01:10:31,102
Oh, it'll look like
an accident all right.

994
01:10:31,137 --> 01:10:33,207
When I find Robertson,
I'm gonna kill him.

995
01:10:33,546 --> 01:10:35,702
Already been there, done that.

996
01:10:41,546 --> 01:10:44,879
Looks like their plan was to jump
out at the end of the mall disaster

997
01:10:44,914 --> 01:10:47,499
like heroes responding to the call.

998
01:10:48,338 --> 01:10:52,166
But I never saw any bodachs
around Eckles, either.

999
01:10:52,505 --> 01:10:56,501
The presence of the bodachs
tipped me off to Fungus Bob...

1000
01:10:56,536 --> 01:11:00,498
but not to his two co-conspirators,
which now seems...

1001
01:11:00,838 --> 01:11:02,346
intentional.

1002
01:11:02,381 --> 01:11:06,540
As if the bodachs knew of my gift,
as if they know I can see them.

1003
01:11:07,922 --> 01:11:10,494
The bodachs have been
manipulating me.

1004
01:11:32,090 --> 01:11:34,046
I'm gonna finish you off,
old man.

1005
01:11:38,633 --> 01:11:39,847
Four.

1006
01:11:39,882 --> 01:11:42,169
Well, that's just jiffy.

1007
01:12:13,551 --> 01:12:16,667
This just so happens
to be my very favorite book.

1008
01:12:17,301 --> 01:12:19,458
The Wonderful Wizard Of Oz.

1009
01:12:19,676 --> 01:12:25,010
Officer Varner Prince of Darkness,
Officer Varner, Prince of Darkness.

1010
01:12:35,094 --> 01:12:36,255
Viola.

1011
01:12:36,469 --> 01:12:38,594
- Viola! What are you doing here?
- Odd! Geez!

1012
01:12:38,629 --> 01:12:40,684
- You scared the-
- What are you doing here?

1013
01:12:40,719 --> 01:12:42,656
We had to pick out
a birthday present for Levanna.

1014
01:12:42,691 --> 01:12:45,142
And Nicolina wanted to get
a card for her big sister.

1015
01:12:45,177 --> 01:12:47,593
Look, your dream, it's happening
right here, right now.

1016
01:12:48,220 --> 01:12:50,990
I thought in a big stadium or
at the water park or a bowling alley.

1017
01:12:51,025 --> 01:12:53,761
Ladies, I need you to take Viola
and get her out of here, okay?

1018
01:12:53,796 --> 01:12:56,464
Come on.
Come on, come on. Go on.

1019
01:12:57,720 --> 01:12:59,561
This made Dorothy so very angry...

1020
01:12:59,596 --> 01:13:01,887
that she picked up the bucket
of water that stood near...

1021
01:13:01,922 --> 01:13:04,590
and dashed it all over
the wicked witch.

1022
01:13:05,512 --> 01:13:08,006
And then the wicked witch said...

1023
01:13:08,041 --> 01:13:10,502
"I'm melting! I'm melting!"

1024
01:13:13,346 --> 01:13:15,917
There's suddenly lots
of flashing lights.

1025
01:13:16,263 --> 01:13:18,833
With old-fashioned kiddie music.

1026
01:13:21,055 --> 01:13:23,010
And then I hear a big crowd.

1027
01:13:25,430 --> 01:13:28,630
And then there's the sound of water,
gushing water.

1028
01:13:32,097 --> 01:13:33,758
Bye, Nell.

1029
01:13:33,793 --> 01:13:35,421
Bye, Stormy.

1030
01:13:37,722 --> 01:13:39,597
Excuse me. Excuse me. Sorry!

1031
01:13:39,632 --> 01:13:41,138
Move, move. Excuse me!

1032
01:14:29,475 --> 01:14:32,177
A gun! He's got a gun!

1033
01:15:25,228 --> 01:15:28,759
Stormy and I are destined
to be together forever.

1034
01:15:29,603 --> 01:15:33,549
Gypsy Mummy gave us a card that
said so, for a single quarter...

1035
01:15:34,187 --> 01:15:36,675
what other couples couldn't
buy at any price.

1036
01:15:40,728 --> 01:15:42,388
No!

1037
01:16:06,272 --> 01:16:08,760
Get out of the way! Get off!

1038
01:17:11,567 --> 01:17:13,024
Hi.

1039
01:17:24,400 --> 01:17:25,728
Odd!

1040
01:17:33,359 --> 01:17:34,687
Odd!

1041
01:17:36,152 --> 01:17:37,728
It's not over.

1042
01:17:44,194 --> 01:17:45,520
It's not over.

1043
01:17:46,152 --> 01:17:48,771
It's not over. It's not over.

1044
01:17:51,694 --> 01:17:54,069
Hey Chief. What's with
the guy who shot the dogs?

1045
01:17:54,104 --> 01:17:56,355
His names Kevin Goss.

1046
01:17:56,778 --> 01:17:58,653
One of these days, bang!

1047
01:17:58,688 --> 01:17:59,814
You hear me?

1048
01:18:21,570 --> 01:18:24,485
He's got a gun!

1049
01:18:39,405 --> 01:18:41,037
- Is this your truck?
- I need a drill!

1050
01:18:41,072 --> 01:18:42,884
Do you have a drill?
I need to get this open!

1051
01:18:42,919 --> 01:18:44,662
- Who the hell are you?
- I'm a cop. Now look!

1052
01:18:44,697 --> 01:18:46,780
You see that woman?
Some maniacs just shot up the mall!

1053
01:18:46,815 --> 01:18:49,072
So either get with me,
get behind me, or get out!

1054
01:18:49,107 --> 01:18:50,648
I got a grinder!

1055
01:19:02,322 --> 01:19:04,812
Oh, my God.

1056
01:19:20,866 --> 01:19:23,782
Everyone get the hell out of here!
Get the hell out!

1057
01:19:23,817 --> 01:19:24,896
Now!

1058
01:20:12,119 --> 01:20:13,231
Hey!

1059
01:20:34,286 --> 01:20:35,530
Shit!

1060
01:20:45,245 --> 01:20:47,947
You really set yourself up, asshole!

1061
01:21:27,122 --> 01:21:29,825
It's cold in the desert.

1062
01:22:16,083 --> 01:22:19,416
I could tell my stuffing
wasn't entirely intact.

1063
01:22:19,451 --> 01:22:21,340
He's awake. He's awake!

1064
01:22:21,375 --> 01:22:24,207
But it was nothing
they couldn't stitch back together.

1065
01:22:31,083 --> 01:22:33,793
Karla told me that the chief
had come through just fine...

1066
01:22:33,828 --> 01:22:36,466
and somehow managed
to spin Fungus Bob's corpse...

1067
01:22:36,501 --> 01:22:40,115
into a bizarre cover story
that kept my secret a secret.

1068
01:22:45,126 --> 01:22:47,300
An FBI expert
on television said that

1069
01:22:47,335 --> 01:22:50,251
if you hadn't gotten
those explosives out of there,

1070
01:22:50,286 --> 01:22:53,133
at least 500 or 600 people
would've died, for sure.

1071
01:22:53,168 --> 01:22:57,114
They told me events at the Green Moon
Mall had made headlines everywhere.

1072
01:22:58,168 --> 01:23:00,658
But I didn't want to read
or see anything about it.

1073
01:23:02,335 --> 01:23:03,217
According to Eckles...

1074
01:23:03,252 --> 01:23:06,440
he and Varner started a satanic
cult when they were teenagers.

1075
01:23:06,475 --> 01:23:09,628
One night, they killed a man
and realized they enjoyed it.

1076
01:23:09,663 --> 01:23:10,927
So they kept at it,

1077
01:23:10,962 --> 01:23:13,876
eventually joining
the police force for better cover.

1078
01:23:14,920 --> 01:23:18,103
They met Robertson and Goss
and came up with a plan...

1079
01:23:18,138 --> 01:23:21,287
to infiltrate a small town
and then slowly kill it.

1080
01:23:32,754 --> 01:23:34,177
Odd! Odd! Odd!

1081
01:23:34,212 --> 01:23:36,701
Detail, present arms.

1082
01:23:37,546 --> 01:23:38,427
ODD SAVES

1083
01:23:38,462 --> 01:23:39,629
MARRY ME ODD!
ODD WORLD

1084
01:23:39,664 --> 01:23:41,786
IN ODD WE TRUST

1085
01:24:02,547 --> 01:24:03,554
When I'm with you,

1086
01:24:03,589 --> 01:24:07,334
I don't have to worry about
pancakes or poltergeists.

1087
01:24:08,381 --> 01:24:11,711
When I'm with you,
I'm with my destiny.

1088
01:24:12,548 --> 01:24:16,162
Where you live, I flourish.

1089
01:24:21,173 --> 01:24:23,662
We ate food that wasn't healthy.

1090
01:24:26,382 --> 01:24:28,871
We drank too much...

1091
01:24:30,549 --> 01:24:32,207
and slept too much...

1092
01:24:38,674 --> 01:24:41,507
but could never kiss enough.

1093
01:24:42,216 --> 01:24:45,048
Everything was just as I wished.

1094
01:24:49,508 --> 01:24:53,668
- Yeah?
- Odd, it's us. Open up.

1095
01:24:55,258 --> 01:24:57,592
- Hey, guys.
- We have been calling you, Oddie.

1096
01:24:57,627 --> 01:24:59,891
I know. You know,
I disconnected the phone...

1097
01:24:59,925 --> 01:25:02,217
because the reporters won't
leave me and Stormy alone.

1098
01:25:02,252 --> 01:25:04,006
- Son.
- Do you want some-

1099
01:25:06,509 --> 01:25:08,797
You've been here long enough.

1100
01:25:08,832 --> 01:25:11,084
We think it's time to stop.

1101
01:25:11,593 --> 01:25:16,499
Sweetheart, the coroner finally
released her poor body.

1102
01:25:33,885 --> 01:25:35,675
A part of me knew...

1103
01:25:36,302 --> 01:25:39,834
from the moment I saw her
behind the ice cream counter.

1104
01:25:40,553 --> 01:25:43,385
But the truth hurt
too much to accept.

1105
01:25:44,511 --> 01:25:47,842
Her death would have been
one wound too many that day.

1106
01:25:49,011 --> 01:25:52,543
And I think I would have
let go of this life.

1107
01:26:04,429 --> 01:26:06,384
She's here, isn't she?

1108
01:26:13,596 --> 01:26:15,254
You got to let her go.

1109
01:26:16,513 --> 01:26:19,427
She deserves to move
to her next life.

1110
01:26:20,680 --> 01:26:22,006
Son...

1111
01:26:24,013 --> 01:26:25,554
it's just time.

1112
01:27:22,141 --> 01:27:23,599
I love you.

1113
01:27:26,183 --> 01:27:30,343
I promise I will see you again.
Okay?

1114
01:28:39,020 --> 01:28:43,575
YOU ARE NOW LEAVING PICO MUNDO
COME BACK AGAIN SOON

1115
01:28:50,563 --> 01:28:53,605
Stormy always believed that life
is not about how fast you run...

1116
01:28:53,640 --> 01:28:55,760
or with what degree of grace.

1117
01:28:56,313 --> 01:28:58,361
That this life is a boot camp,

1118
01:28:58,396 --> 01:29:00,936
that we must persevere
through all the obstacles

1119
01:29:00,971 --> 01:29:03,478
and hardships to earn our way
into the next life.

1120
01:29:04,522 --> 01:29:07,768
To be with her again, I will have
the perseverance of a bulldog.

1121
01:29:09,230 --> 01:29:12,347
But sometimes, it seems to me...

1122
01:29:13,189 --> 01:29:16,306
the training
is unnecessarily painful.

1123
01:29:23,606 --> 01:29:25,654
If I live an average life-span...

1124
01:29:25,689 --> 01:29:29,020
I'll have another 60 years
before I see Stormy again.

1125
01:29:29,523 --> 01:29:31,313
That will be a long wait.

1126
01:29:33,398 --> 01:29:35,354
But I am a patient man.

1127
01:29:37,773 --> 01:29:40,060
And I have much to do.

